A: The error is because you are trying to access an index that does not exist in the TypedArray. The length of the TypedArray is the number of elements it contains, and the indices are 0-based, meaning the last index is length-1.
So, if the length of the TypedArray is 3, the valid indices are 0, 1, and 2. If you try to access index 3, you will get an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException.
You can solve this by checking if the index is less than the length of the TypedArray before trying to access it:
for (int k = 0; k < typedArray.length(); k++) {
    if (k < typedArray.length()) {
        MenuItem = typedArray.getString(k);
        if (k == 0) {
            Log.e("String from" + str, MenuItem);
        }
    }
}

This will prevent you from trying to access an index that does not exist in the TypedArray.

